    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>it's not just being tired though. it's more like... the well is actually dry. i've spent my whole life pouring myself into this, and now there is just nothing left to pour. it feels like i'm just a hollow shell performing a role that i've already mastered and finished. what's the point of a book that's already been told? it just feels like i'm dragging out the ending for no reason.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
